works.description: Calling all the well-heeled champagne lovers! Two bottles of the world’s oldest champagne, which was recently found in a shipwreck in the Baltic Sea, will be up for auction this summer. Finland’s autonomous province of Aaland will sell the 200-year-old bottles in an exclusive champagne auction taking place in the capital Mariehamn on June 3, 2011. While one of the bottles comes from Veuve Clicquot, the other one is from the now extinct house of Juglar.
